==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Arian
<hw>A"ri*an</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Arianus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to Arius, a presbyter of the
church of Alexandria, in the fourth century, or to the doctrines of
Arius, who held Christ to be inferior to God the Father in nature and
dignity, though the first and noblest of all created beings.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One who adheres to or believes the doctrines of
Arius.</def></def2> <rj><au>Mosheim.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arianism</ent>⟦br⟧
